15}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=3 | [[Italy national football team|Italy national team]]\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2008||1||0\n|-\n|2009||1||0\n|-\n|2010||4||0\n|-\n|2011||8||0\n|-\n|2012||8||0\n|-\n|2013||11||0\n|-\n|2014||1||0\n|-\n!Total||34||0\n|}\n\n== Honours ==\n\n=== Club ===\n;Napoli<ref name=SW>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/christian-maggio/4147/|title=C. Maggio|publisher=Soccerway|accessdate=17 December 2015}}</ref>\n*[[Coppa Italia]] (2): [[2011\u201312 Coppa Italia|2011\u201312]], [[2013\u201314 Coppa Italia|2013\u201314]]\n*[[Supercoppa Italiana]] (1): [[2014 Supercoppa Italiana|2014]]\n\n=== International ===\n;Italy<ref name=SW/>\n*[[UEFA European Championship]]: Runner-up [[UEFA Euro 2012|2012]]\n*[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]: Third Place [[FIFA Confederations Cup|2013]]\n\n=== Individual ===\n*[[Oscar del Calcio]] - [[Serie A Team of the Year]] (3): 2010\u201311,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aia-figc.it/dettaglio.asp?ID=6050 |title=Gran Cala' del Calcio 2011: Rizzoli premiato miglior arbitro |publisher=FIGC.it |language=Italian |date=24 January 2012 |accessdate=21 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103212125/http://aia-figc.it/dettaglio.asp?ID=6050 |archivedate=3 November 2013 |df=dmy }}</ref> 2011\u201312,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/calcio/serie_a/2013/01/27-242192/Gran+Gal%26%23224%3B+del+Calcio+Aic.+E%26apos%3B+Pirlo+il+migliore+del+2012|title=Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio Aic. E' Pirlo il migliore del 2012|trans-title=Gran Gal\u00e0 del Calcio Aic. Pirlo is the best of 2012|publisher=Tutto Sport|language=Italian|date=27 January 2013|accessdate=1 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150624042901/http://www.tuttosport.com/calcio/serie_a/2013/01/27-242192/Gran+Gal%26%23224%3B+del+Calcio+Aic.+E%26apos%3B+Pirlo+il+migliore+del+2012|archive-date=24 June 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> 2012\u201313<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttosport.com/calcio/serie_a/2014/01/27-283890/Oscar+del+calcio%3A+Vidal+e+Pirlo+sono+il+top.+La+Juve+%C3%A8+la+pi%C3%B9+forte+d%27Italia?print|title=Oscar del calcio: Vidal e Pirlo sono il top. La Juve \u00e8 la pi\u00f9 forte d'Italia|publisher=Tuttosport|language=Italian|date=27 January 2014|accessdate=19 June 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150620001027/http://www.tuttosport.com/calcio/serie_a/2014/01/27-283890/Oscar+del+calcio%3A+Vidal+e+Pirlo+sono+il+top.+La+Juve+%C3%A8+la+pi%C3%B9+forte+d%27Italia?print|archive-date=20 June 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150315033310/http://www.sscnapoli.it/Squadra/Christian-Maggio Player profile] on Napoli's official website {{in lang|it}}\n* {{FIFA|210199}}\n* {{UEFA|54105}}\n* [http://aic.football.it/scheda/164 Player profile] at AIC {{in lang|it}}\n* [http://www.figc.it/nazionali/DettaglioConvocato?codiceConvocato=2066&squadra=1 Player profile] at FIGC {{in lang|it}}\n* {{Soccerway|christian-maggio/4147}}\n\n{{Navboxes colour\n|title=Awards\n|bg=gold\n|fg=navy\n|list1=\n{{2010\u201311 Serie A Team of the Year}}\n{{2011\u201312 Serie A Team of the Year}}\n{{2012\u201313 Serie A Team of the Year}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes colour\n| title = Italy squads\n| bg = #0066bc\n| fg = white\n| bordercolor = silver\n| list1 =\n{{Italy squad 2010 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Italy squad UEFA Euro 2012}}\n{{Italy squad 2013 FIFA Confederations Cup}}\n}}\n{{Benevento Calcio squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maggio, Christian}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Italian footballers]]\n[[Category:L.R. Vicenza Virtus players]]\n[[Category:ACF Fiorentina players]]\n[[Category:A.C.D. Treviso players]]\n[[Category:U.C. Sampdoria players]]\n[[Category:S.S.C. Napoli players]]\n[[Category:Benevento Calcio players]]\n[[Category:Serie A players]]\n[[Category:Serie B players]]\n[[Category:Association football wingers]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Vicenza]]\n[[Category:Italy youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Italy international footballers]]\n[[Category:2010 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2012 players]]\n[[Category:2013 FIFA Confederations Cup players]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games silver medalists for Italy]]\n[[Category:Mediterranean Games medalists in football]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2001 Mediterranean Games]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2014}}\n{{BLP sources|date=June 2011}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name               = Christian Maggio\n| image              = Christian Maggio BGR-ITA 2012.jpg\n| image_size         = 200\n| caption            = Maggio with [[Italy national football team|Italy]] in 2012\n| fullname           = Christian Maggio<ref>{{cite web|title=FIFA World Cup South Africa 2010&nbsp;\u2013 List of Players|url=https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/competition/01/22/85/78/fwc_2010_squadlists.pdf|publisher=F\u00e9d\u00e9ration Internationale de Football Association (FIFA)|accessdate=5 June 2013|format=PDF}}</ref>\n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|1982|2|11|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[Montecchio Maggiore]], Italy\n| height             = {{height|meter=1.84}}<ref>{{cite web|title=Christian Maggio \u2013 Profile|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/players/player=210199/index.html|work=Confederations Cup Brazil 2013|publisher=[[FIFA]].com|accessdate=21 January 2014}}</ref>\n| position           = [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|Right-back]] / [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|Wing-back]]\n| currentclub        = [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]]\n| clubnumber         = 11\n| youthyears1        = 1997\u20132000 |youthclubs1 = [[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]]\n| years1             = 2000\u20132003 |clubs1      = [[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]]               |caps1 = 38  |goals1 = 1\n| years2             = 2003\u20132006 |clubs2      = [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]            |caps2 = 58 |goals2 = 2\n| years3             = 2006      |clubs3      = \u2192 [[A.S.D. Treviso 2009|Treviso]] (loan) |caps3 = 11  |goals3 = 0\n| years4             = 2006\u20132008 |clubs4      = [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]             |caps4 = 60  |goals4 = 11\n| years5             = 2008\u20132018     |clubs5      = [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]]                 |caps5 = 233 |goals5 = 20\n| years6             = 2018\u2013    |clubs6      = [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]]                 |caps6 = 38 |goals6 = 5\n| nationalyears1 = 2000\u20132001 |nationalteam1 = [[Italy national under-18 football team|Italy U18]]                                         |nationalcaps1 = 5  |nationalgoals1 = 1\n| nationalyears2 = 2000\u20132002 |nationalteam2 = [[Italy national under-20 football team|Italy U20]] |nationalcaps2 = 24 |nationalgoals2 = 3\n| nationalyears3 = 2002      |nationalteam3 = [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy U21]] |nationalcaps3 = 2  |nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2008\u20132014     |nationalteam4 = [[Italy national football team|Italy]]               |nationalcaps4 = 34 |nationalgoals4 = 0\n| medaltemplates = {{MedalCountry|{{ITA}}}}{{MedalSport|Association football}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[UEFA European Football Championship|UEFA Euro]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[UEFA Euro 2012|Poland & Ukraine 2012]]|}}\n{{MedalCompetition |[[FIFA Confederations Cup]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[FIFA Confederations Cup 2013|Brazil 2013]]|}}\n| club-update         = 09:54, 1 February 2020 (UTC)\n| ntupdate            = 5 March 2014\n}}\n\n'''Christian Maggio''' ({{IPA-it|\u02c8kristjam \u02c8madd\u0292o}}; born 11 February 1982) is an Italian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]], as a [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]], or as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right winger]] for [[Serie B]] club [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.beneventocalcio.club/news/notizie/1280/formalizzati-gli-accordi-con-gori-maggio-e-nocerino.shtml|title=Formalizzati gli accordi con Gori, Maggio e Nocerino|last=|first=|date=7 July 2018|work=Benevento Calcio|access-date=7 July 2018|language=it}}</ref>\n\nA dynamic and hard-working offensive full-back, prior to joining Napoli in 2008, Maggio played for Italian clubs [[Vicenza Calcio|Vicenza]], [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]], [[A.S.D. Treviso 2009|Treviso]], and [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]]. With Napoli he has won two [[Coppa Italia]] titles and the [[Supercoppa Italiana]]. After a decade with the club, he joined [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]] in 2018.\n\nA former Italy international level, he represented the [[Italy national football team]] on 34 occasions between 2008 and 2014, and took part at the [[2010 FIFA World Cup]], [[UEFA Euro 2012]] (winning a silver medal), and the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup]] (winning a bronze medal).\n\n== Club career ==\n=== Vicenza ===\nMaggio began his career at [[Vicenza]] making his [[Serie A]] debut in the [[2000\u201301 Serie A|2000\u20132001 season]], finishing the campaign with six appearances.<ref>http://www.sscnapoli.it/client/render_e.aspx?root=1034&content=0</ref> However, despite some success on a personal level, Vicenza were subsequently relegated to [[Serie B]] at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesi/ital01.html |title=Italy 2000/01 |publisher=Rsssf.com |date=1 September 2005}}</ref> Maggio stayed with Vicenza until 2003, making 38 appearances in total while managing to score just 1 goal. Half of the registration rights were also sold to Parma in June 2002<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/CalcioMercato2002.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118213559/http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/CalcioMercato2002.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 November 2007|title=Wayback Machine|date=18 November 2007|publisher=}}</ref> for 4 billion [[Italian lira|lire]] (\u20ac2.066 million,<ref>AC Parma SpA Report and Accounts on 30 June 2002 {{in lang|it}}</ref> for an undisclosed cash plus [[Paolo Guastalvino]]). In June 2003 the co-ownership deal was renewed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/partecipazioni2003.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118213220/http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/partecipazioni2003.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 November 2007|title=Wayback Machine|date=18 November 2007|publisher=}}</ref>\n\n=== Fiorentina ===\nIn 2003, Maggio signed for [[ACF Fiorentina]] from Parma. In June 2004 Fiorentina acquired another half from Vicenza.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/partecipazioni2004.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071118213315/http://www.lega-calcio.it/ita/partecipazioni2004.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=18 November 2007|title=Wayback Machine|date=18 November 2007|publisher=}}</ref> Maggio appeared regularly for Fiorentina until they were promoted from [[Serie B]] to [[Serie A]] during the [[2003\u201304 Serie B|2003\u201304]] season. During the [[2004\u201305 Serie A|2004\u201305 season]], he played 13 times, while in the [[2005\u201306 Serie A]] season, he only appeared 3 times due to injury; in January 2006, he was loaned to [[A.S.D. Treviso 2009|Treviso]] in order to gain playing time, making 11 appearances, although the club was relegated at the end of the season. Overall, Maggio played 56 games for ''The Viola'', scoring 2 goals over a 4-year period, including spending 1.5 seasons on loan. Maggio was loaned to Sampdoria for \u20ac150,000 in the [[2006\u201307 Serie A|2006\u201307]] season.<ref>ACF Fiorentina SpA Report and Accounts on 31 December 2006 {{in lang|it}}</ref><ref name=Fiorentina2007bilancio>ACF Fiorentina SpA Report and Accounts on 31 December 2007 {{in lang|it}}</ref> At the end of loan Sampdoria signed him in another [[co-ownership (football)|co-ownership deal]] for \u20ac1.5 million.<ref name=Fiorentina2007bilancio/>\n\n=== Sampdoria ===\nHowever, it was not until Maggio signed for [[U.C. Sampdoria]] that he began to fulfil the potential he had shown when playing for Italy at youth level. Some very impressive performances during the [[2007\u201308 Serie A|2007\u201308]] season resulted in nine goals from twenty-nine appearances. At the end of season Sampdoria acquired another half for \u20ac1.95 million.<ref>ACF Fiorentina SpA Report and Accounts on 31 December 2008 {{in lang|it}}</ref> He was immediately re-sold to [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]] for \u20ac8 million.<ref>S.S.C. Napoli S.p.A. ''bilancio'' (financial report and accounts) on 30 June 2009 (in Italian), [http://www.registroimprese.it PDF purchased from Italian C.C.I.A.A.]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sampdoria.it/news/comunicato-stampa-maggio-passa-ufficialmente-al-napoli.html|title=Comunicato stampa: Maggio passa ufficialmente al Napoli|publisher=UC Sampdoria|language=Italian|date=11 June 2008|accessdate=15 April 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140416224523/http://www.sampdoria.it/news/comunicato-stampa-maggio-passa-ufficialmente-al-napoli.html|archivedate=16 April 2014|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Napoli ===\nDuring his time at Napoli he has continued to perform consistently. 18 October 2009 saw Maggio score a 90th-minute goal to help seal a 2\u20131 comeback victory over [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]], as [[Fabio Quagliarella]] had scored a late equaliser for the hosts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=278517&cc=5901 |title=Gamecast: Napoli v Bologna \u2013 Italian Serie A \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=18 October 2009}}</ref> Maggio continued his good form as he scored the only goal of the game on 25 October, helping Napoli defeat [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]] at the [[Stadio Artemio Franchi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=278504&cc=5901 |title=Gamecast: Fiorentina v Napoli \u2013 Italian Serie A \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=25 October 2009}}</ref> On 24 January 2010 Maggio scored a wonderful volley against Livorno. He took up a position near the corner of the penalty area as a long cross-field pass descended towards him.  As this raking pass came across his body from his left shoulder he volleyed it first time, with great power, swerving over the goalkeeper into the top corner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=278557&cc=5901 |title=Gamecast: Livorno v Napoli \u2013 Italian Serie A \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=24 January 2010}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 December 2010, Maggio scored a last gasp goal which saw Napoli secure all three points in a 1\u20130 defeat of [[U.S. Citt\u00e0 di Palermo|Palermo]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/match/48815/napoli-vs-palermo/preview |title=Napoli vs Palermo Preview |publisher=Goal.com |date=}}</ref>\nDuring this period, Maggio usually functioned as a right midfielder/winger for Napoli in a [[Formation (association football)|3\u20134\u20132\u20131]] formation under manager [[Walter Mazzarri]]. He had initially played at right back for the majority of his career; however, since he started playing as a right winger, the quality of his performances improved, and he particularly excelled in this new position due to his attacking skills.\n\nDuring the [[2011\u201312 Serie A|2011\u201312 season]], his performances and attacking abilities continued to improve, as he netted three goals and provided five assists in 33 league games for Napoli.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/player/_/id/25030/christian-maggio?cc=5901 |title=Christian Maggio Bio, Stats, News \u2013 Football / Soccer \u2013 - ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=11 February 1982}}</ref> Maggio provided assists for two of his side's goals in their enthralling 3\u20133 draw with [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]] on 29 November 2011.<ref>{{cite web|author=Serie A+00:00, 29 November, 2011San Paolo, Italy |url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=327100&cc=5901 |title=Gamecast: Napoli v Juventus \u2013 Italian Serie A \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=29 November 2011}}</ref> In the second leg of Napoli's [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League knockout phase|Round of 16]] tie with eventual winners [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]], Maggio limped off the field in the 37th minute with an injury.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lawton |first=Matt |url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2115030/Chelsea-4-Napoli-1-AET-agg-5-4--Blues-qualify-Champions-League-quarter-finals.html |title=Chelsea 4 Napoli 1 AET (agg 5\u20134): Blues qualify for Champions League quarter-finals &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=15 March 2012}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=December 2019}} Napoli eventually lost 5\u20134 on aggregate after extra time,<ref>{{cite web|author=Daniel Taylor at Stamford Bridge |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/mar/14/chelsea-napoli-champions-league |title=Chelsea 4\u20131 Napoli (Chelsea win 5\u20134 on agg) &#124; Champions League last-16 &#124; Football |publisher=The Guardian |date=}}</ref> as Maggio missed the next seven games and his side only won once. He helped his team to win the [[2011\u201312 Coppa Italia]] that season over Serie A champions [[Juventus F.C.|Juventus]]; this was Napoli's first trophy since 1990, under [[Diego Armando Maradona|Maradona]]. His performances led to him being named in 2011\u201312 Serie A Team of the Season, the first such honour of his career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goal.com/en/news/1717/editorial/2012/05/14/3098597/serie-a-team-of-the-season-pirlo-ibrahimovic-di-natale-star# |title=Serie A Team of the Season: Pirlo, Ibrahimovic & Di Natale star in the 2011\u201312 campaign |publisher=Goal.com |date=14 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nMaggio left Napoli in May 2018 after a decade at the club, during which time he made over 300 appearances and became the player with the sixth-highest number of appearances for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.calciomercato.com/en/news/report-napoli-eye-de-silvestri-823884|title=REPORT: Napoli eye Sampdoria wingback De Silvestri|publisher=www.calciomercato.com|date=15 May 2018}}</ref>\n\n===Benevento===\nOn 6 July 2018, Maggio signed with [[Serie B]] club [[Benevento Calcio|Benevento]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.corrieredellosport.it/news/calcio/calcio-mercato/2018/07/06-45077449/calciomercato_benevento_ufficiale_hanno_firmato_maggio_nocerino_e_gori/|access-date=6 July 2018|title=Maggio signed with Benevento|website=Corriere dello Sport.it}}</ref>\n\n== International career ==\nAfter missing out on a potential call-up for [[UEFA Euro 2008]] under manager [[Roberto Donadoni]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://kr.goal.com/it/Articolo.aspx?ContenutoId=705392|title=Continuano i musi lunghi per le mancate convocazioni in Azzurro. Ora tocca a Maggio: \"Non ci speravo, ma ci sono rimasto male\"|work=goal.com|language=Italian|date=21 May 2008|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> Maggio was first called up to the national team by [[Marcello Lippi]] for the team's [[2010 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] matches in October 2008,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2008/10/sezioni/sport/calcio/nazionale/convocati-ottobre/convocati-ottobre/convocati-ottobre.html|title=Maggio, Pepe, Rossi e Santacroce sono quattro i nomi nuovi di Lippi|publisher=[[La Repubblica]]|language=Italian|date=5 October 2008|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> but only made his debut with the [[Italy national football team|Italy]] on 19 November 2008, at the age of 26, in a 1\u20131 friendly draw against [[Greece national football team|Greece]], coming on as a substitute for [[Mauro Camoranesi]] in the 61st minute.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/report?id=256024&cc=5901 |title=Gamecast: Greece v Italy \u2013 International Friendly \u2013 ESPN FC |publisher=Soccernet.espn.go.com |date=19 November 2008}}</ref> He made his first start with the national team on 18 November 2009, in a friendly match against [[Sweden national football team|Sweden]] held in Cesena.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.repubblica.it/2009/11/sport/calcio/nazionale/italia-svezia/italia-svezia-diretta/italia-svezia-diretta.html|title=Italia promossa \"Il gruppo c'\u00e8\"|publisher=La Repubblica|language=Italian|date=18 November 2009|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> He took part at the [[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010 World Cup]];<ref>{{cite web|author=Featured Columnist |url=http://bleacherreport.com/articles/400032-2010-fifa-world-cup-lippi-names-italy-squad-the-champ-is-here |title=2010 FIFA World Cup: Lippi Names Italy Squad...The Champ Is Here! |publisher=Bleacher Report |date=2 June 2010}}</ref> although he was initially called up as the back-up for [[Gianluca Zambrotta]], he played in the nation's third group stage match on 24 June, a 3\u20132 loss to [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]], coming on for [[Domenico Criscito]] at half-time; due to the defeat, Italy were eliminated in the first round of the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/competitions/world-cup-2010/news/7847212/Slovakia-3-Italy-2-match-report.html |title=Slovakia 3 Italy 2: match report |publisher=Telegraph |date=}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Christian Maggio and Ashley Young England-Italy Euro 2012.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Maggio battling England's [[Ashley Young]] for the ball during their quarterfinal match-up at [[UEFA Euro 2012|Euro 2012]]]]\nAfter being briefly being excluded from the national side, he was called up by new head coach [[Cesare Prandelli]] on 6 February 2011 for a friendly match against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] held in Dortmund,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Calcio/Nazionale/06-02-2011/italia-torna-buffon-c-matri-8062086316.shtml|title=Italia: torna Buffon, c'\u00e8 Matri In Germania anche Thiago Motta|publisher=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|language=Italian|date=6 February 2011|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> and subsequently he became a regular for the team in the right back position under the manager; as a result, he was named to the 23-man Italy squad that took part at the [[UEFA Euro 2012]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/euro2012/article-2151509/Euro-2012-Cesare-Prandelli-explains-Domenico-Criscitos-exclusion-Italy-squad.html |title=Euro 2012: Cesare Prandelli explains Domenico Criscito's exclusion from Italy squad &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=29 May 2012}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=December 2019}} Maggio appeared in the first two group games for Italy at the Euros, a 1\u20131 draw with holders [[Spain national football team|Spain]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18180099 |title=BBC Sport \u2013 Euro 2012: Spain 1\u20131 Italy |publisher=BBC.co.uk |last=Smith |first=Ben|date=10 June 2012}}</ref> and another 1\u20131 draw with [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], playing as a wing-back on the right in a 3\u20135\u20132 formation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/euro2012/article-2159412/Euro-2012-results-Italy-1-Croatia-1-Mario-Mandzukic-cancels-Andrea-Pirlos-pearler.html |title=Euro 2012 results Italy 1 Croatia 1 Mario Mandzukic cancels out Andrea Pirlo's pearler &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |last=Walker |first=Michael |date=14 June 2012}}</ref>{{deprecated inline|certain=yes|date=December 2019}} Maggio also appeared as a substitute in Italy's 4\u20132 penalty shootout victory over [[England national football team|England]] in the quarterfinals, following a 0\u20130 draw after extra-time, playing as a right-back in a 4\u20133\u20131\u20132 after coming on for [[Ignazio Abate]] in the 90th minute; during the match, however, he received his second booking of the tournament, which ruled him out of the semi-final fixture against [[Germany national football team|Germany]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/18355305 |title=BBC Sport \u2013 England 0\u20130 Italy (2\u20134 on pens) |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |last=McNulty |first=Phil |date=24 June 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2012/jun/24/england-italy-euro-2012-live|title=England v Italy: Euro 2012 quarter-final \u2013 as it happened|publisher=The Guardian|author1=Jacob Steinberg|date=24 June 2012|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nMaggio was also named to the 23-man Italy squad that participated in the [[2013 FIFA Confederations Cup|2013 Confederations Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.figc.it/it/204/36469/2013/06/News.shtml|title=Inviata alla FIFA la lista per la Confederations Cup: c\u2019\u00e8 anche Barzagli|publisher=FIGC|language=Italian|date=3 June 2013|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> He made his tournament debut in Italy's second group match of the tournament, a 4\u20133 win over [[Japan national football team|Japan]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=255199/match=300222456/summary.html |title=Italy edge Japan in thriller to reach semis |publisher=FIFA |date=19 June 2013 |accessdate=4 May 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150505062123/http://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round%3D255199/match%3D300222456/summary.html |archivedate=5 May 2015 |df=dmy }}</ref> and hit the cross-bar with a header in a 4\u20132 defeat to hosts and eventual champions [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] in the final group match after coming on as a substitute.<ref>{{cite web|title=Italy 2-4 Brazil: Fred fires Selecao to top spot in Group A |url=http://www.goal.com/en/match/97894/italy-vs-brazil/report? |publisher=Goal.com |date=22 June 2013 |accessdate=24 August 2013 }}</ref> He also started in the semi-final match against Spain, helping the team to keep a cleansheet, although Spain would advance to the final with a 7\u20136 victory penalties, following a 0\u20130 deadlock after extra-time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=255207/match=300222468/summary.html|title=Spain edge dramatic shootout to reach Final|publisher=FIFA|date=27 June 2013|accessdate=4 May 2015}}</ref> He once again started in the third-place match against Uruguay, where he helped the Italians to capture the bronze medal, following a 5\u20134 victory in the resulting penalty shoot-out after a 2\u20132 draw following extra-time.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Nazionale/confederations_cup/30-06-2013/confederations-italia-uruguay-5-4-rigori-buffon-ne-para-tre-azzurri-terzi-20688727871.shtml|title=Confederations, Italia-Uruguay 5-4 dopo i rigori, Buffon ne para tre, azzurri terzi|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|author1=Riccardo Pratesi|date=30 June 2013|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\nMaggio was named in Prandelli's provisional 30-man squad for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], but was one of seven players cut from the final squad, after missing much of the previous season due to injury.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27402363|title=World Cup 2014: Italy omit Giuseppe Rossi from final squad|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=1 June 2014|accessdate=3 June 2014}}</ref> On 18 March 2015, he announced his retirement from the Italian national side at the age of 33; in total he made 34 appearances for Italy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivoazzurro.it/news/maggio-lascia-la-nazionale-azzurro-7-anni-di-grandi-emozioni/|title=Maggio lascia la Nazionale: \"In Azzurro, 7 anni di grandi emozioni\"|publisher=VivoAzzurro.it|language=Italian|date=18 March 2015|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Style of play ==\nA dynamic, hard-working and tenacious right-footed player, with an eye for goal, for the majority of his career Maggio has been deployed as an attacking-minded [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|full-back]] or [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|wing-back]] on the right flank in a four-man back-line, although his preferred role is that of [[Midfielder#Winger|right-sided wide midfielder or winger]] in a [[Formation (association football)#3\u20135\u20132|3\u20135\u20132 formation]], a position which allows him both to make attacking runs up the wing, or late runs into the area, and also to track back, thus enabling him to cover the right side of the pitch effectively.<ref name=\"Cristian Maggio uno dei migliori esterni d\u2019Europa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ciaosport.it/calciatori/cristian-maggio-uno-dei-migliori-esterni-deuropa/|title=Cristian Maggio uno dei migliori esterni d\u2019Europa|publisher=CiaoSport.it|language=Italian|author1=Claudio Gervasio|date=6 January 2012|accessdate=14 July 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151223190748/http://www.ciaosport.it/calciatori/cristian-maggio-uno-dei-migliori-esterni-deuropa/|archive-date=23 December 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"Senza Mazzarri rischia grosso, il destino di Maggio \u00e8 nelle mani di Benitez\">{{cite web|url=http://www.calcionapoli24.it/primo_piano/senza-mazzarri-rischia-grosso-il-destino-di-maggio-e-nelle-mani-di-n128067.html|title=Senza Mazzarri rischia grosso, il destino di Maggio \u00e8 nelle mani di Benitez: tante perplessit\u00e0, sar\u00e0 rivoluzione esterni?|publisher=CalcioNapoli24.it|language=Italian|accessdate=2 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tuttonapoli.net/rassegna-stampa/nel-napoli-grande-con-le-grandi-brilla-la-stella-di-christian-maggio-72051|title=Nel Napoli \"grande con le grandi\" brilla la stella di Christian Maggio|publisher=Tutto Napoli|language=Italian|date=27 October 2011|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"gnarly Napoli\">{{cite web|url=https://www.fourfourtwo.com/features/why-gnarly-napoli-will-prove-tough-crack-arsenal|title=Why gnarly Napoli will prove tough to crack for Arsenal|publisher=FourFourTwo|author1=Michael Cox|date=1 October 2013|accessdate=6 January 2018}}</ref> Nicknamed \"Super-bike\",<ref name=200presenze>{{cite web|url=http://www.spazionapoli.it/2012/01/15/200-presenze-in-serie-a-napoli-si-inchina-davanti-a-maggio/|title=200 presenze in serie A: Napoli si inchina davanti a Maggio|publisher=SpazioNapoli.it|language=Italian|date=15 January 2012|accessdate=14 July 2016}}</ref> due to his composure, pace, positioning, anticipation and stamina, he is capable of aiding his team both offensively and defensively.<ref name=\"Cristian Maggio uno dei migliori esterni d\u2019Europa\"/><ref name=\"gnarly Napoli\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.areanapoli.it/squadra/christian_maggio.html|title=Caratteristiche tecniche di Maggio|publisher=areanapoli.it|language=Italian|accessdate=14 September 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archiviostorico.gazzetta.it/2002/maggio/17/Quanti_nomi_segnare_questa_Under_ga_0_0205176179.shtml|title=Quanti nomi da segnare in questa Under 20|publisher=La Gazzetta dello Sport|language=Italian|date=17 May 2002|accessdate=14 September 2014}}</ref> Maggio is a strong, modern full-back, and an athletic player, who is good in the air; he also possesses good technique, tackling, tactical intelligence, [[Cross (football)|crossing]] ability, and distribution.<ref name=\"Cristian Maggio uno dei migliori esterni d\u2019Europa\"/><ref name=\"Senza Mazzarri rischia grosso, il destino di Maggio \u00e8 nelle mani di Benitez\"/><ref name=\"gnarly Napoli\"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.napolitoday.it/sport/ssc-napoli/christian-maggio-the-indipendent-dani-alves.html|title=Anteprima, stampa inglese pazza di Maggio: \"E' inferiore solo a Dani Alves\"|publisher=napolitoday.it|language=Italian|accessdate=2 December 2014}}</ref>\n\n== Career statistics ==\n=== Club ===\n:''As of match played 5 October 2019.''<ref name=SW/>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"2\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|International\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps