{"title_page": "Shibu (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 Indian Malayalam-language film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = October 2019}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date = October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shibu\n| image          = Shibu movie poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Shibu movie poster\n| director       = Arjun Prabhakaran & Gokul Ramakrishnan\n| producer       = Kaargo Cinemas\n| screenplay     = Arjun , Gokul & Praneesh Vijayan\n| story          = \n| starring       = [[Karthik Ramakrishnan]] <br/> [[Anju Kurian]] <br/>[[Salim Kumar]] <br/> [[Biju Kuttan]]\n| music          = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| cinematography = Shabeer Ahammed\n| editing        = Noufal Abdullah\n| studio         = Kaargo Cinemas\n| distributor    = UK studios\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|19|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 122 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Malayalam\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|50|L}}\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|95|L}}\n}}\n'''''Shibu'''''  is a 2019 Indian [[Malayalam]]-language film directed by duo directors Arjun Prabhakaran & Gokul Ramakrishnan, written by Praneesh and produced by Kaargo Cinemas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/the-story-of-dileep-fan-releases-its-first-look-poster-malayalam-news-212229|title='Aravindante Athidhikal' release date is here! - Malayalam News|date=2018-04-23|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.southlive.in/movie/film-news/shibu-malayalam-movie-teaser-is-out/|title=\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d46 \u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2e\u0d28\u0d4b\u0d39\u0d30\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41; \u0d1f\u0d40\u0d38\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d {{!}} Southlive Malayalam: Kerala News, Malayalam News, Breaking News, Movie News, Political News|last=jo|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> It features an [[ensemble cast]] led by Karthik, [[Anju Kurian]], [[Salim Kumar]], [[Biju Kuttan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-details/shibu/movieshow/69968971.cms|title='Shibu malayalam movie' times of india article}}</ref> [[Sachin Warrier]] composed the music for the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://malayalam.indianexpress.com/entertainment/dileep-fan-movie-shibu-first-look/|title=\u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d4d \u0d06\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u2018\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41\u2019 \u0d0e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41|date=2018-04-23|website=Indian Express Malayalam|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> and Movie was released on July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/shibu-to-release-this-june-news-malayalam-tf3jLjfegifeh.html|title='Shibu' to release this June|website=Sify|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/movies/movie-news/2019/06/04/shibu-malayalam-movie-trailer.html|title=\u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d4d \u0d06\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02; \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 \u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d46\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d|website=ManoramaOnline|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nShibu(Played by Karthik Ramakrishnan) is a young guy from small town who is an aspiring film maker, he tries hard to achieve his dreams, but gets rejected by all.Then he hears about a Film institute and he manages to convince his family and joins film institute.There he instead of learning about cinema gets confused. Later he met with a girl named Kalyani ([[Anju Kurian]]) in a match-making meet and how their aspirations brings them together forms rest of the story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianetnews.com/topic/shibu-movie|title=shibu movie: Latest News, Photos, Videos on shibu movie {{!}} Asianetnews.com|website=www.asianetnews.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vellinakshatram.com/online/news/shibu-malayalam-movie-traile_2019-06-04.php|title=\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d47\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d28\u0d46 \u0d12\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d2f\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d46\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f \u0d24\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d4b ? : \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 \u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d46\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d7c \u0d0e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f !!!|website=www.vellinakshatram.com/online/|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\nIn 2018 Arjun and Gokul, who debuted with the movie '[[32aam Adhyayam 23aam Vaakyam]]' is all set to start working on their next project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nowrunning.com/movie/22623/malayalam/shibu/|title=Shibu (2019) Shibu Malayalam Movie|website=NOWRUNNING|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Titled 'Shibu movie' The film has music by Sachin Warrier. Sachin wrote about it, \"\u2018Omal Kanmani\u2019 composed by Bijibal sir from the 2015 movie \u201832aam Adhyayam 23aam Vaakyam\u2019 is a song that's close to heart among the ones I\u2019ve sung so far. The directors of the movie, Arjun and Gokul came to me to narrate a story recently, and I had a lot of fun listening to it. I believe it'll turn out to be an interesting film. Super happy to associate with Arjun and Gokul, as a composer in their second film\" says Sachin Warrier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desimartini.com/news/malayalam/director-duo-gokul-and-arjun-to-work-on-their-next-film-article75395.htm|title=Director duo Gokul And Arjun To Work On Their Next Film|date=2018-02-02|website=Desimartini|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.malayalamcinema.com/movies/profile/shibu|title=malayalamcinema.com, Official website of AMMA, Malayalam Film news, Malayalam Movie Actors & Actress, Upcoming Malayalam movies|website=www.malayalamcinema.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> Arun Gopi director of [[Dileep]] starer movie [[Ramaleela]] released first look poster of the film on April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/another-hardcore-fan-based-movie-this-time-for-dileep/articleshow/63921957.cms|title=Another hardcore fan based movie, this time for Dileep - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> Actor  [[Dileep]] released trailer of the film on june 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://onlookersmedia.in/videos/dileep-releases-trailer-shibu/|title=Dileep releases the trailer of Shibu|last=Madhu|first=Vignesh|date=2019-06-04|website=onlookersmedia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianetnews.com/entertainment/dileep-releases-teaser-of-shibu--pp0mb6|title=\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2a\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e\u0d41 '\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41'\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d1f\u0d40\u0d38\u0d7c|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Karthik Ramakrishnan as Shibu\n* [[Anju Kurian]] as Kalyani\n* [[Salim Kumar]] as Dr. Thomas\n* [[Biju Kuttan]] as Prahladhan\n* Lukman Lukku as Habeeb\n*[[Vinod Kovoor|Vinod kovoor]] as Producer\n* Unni Rajan P Dev as Antappan\n*[[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Kalyanis friend\n* Aiswarya Padmakumar as Suhara\n*[[Rajesh Sharma (Malayalam actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Satheesh Kupleri\n*[[Kannan|Kannan Sagar]] as Bhuvanan\n*Badra as Shibu's Mom\n*Kshama Krishnan as Sheeba\n*Sharan as Siddique\n*Sundarpandiyan as Police Officer\n* [[Kochu Preman]] as Eastman Narayanan\n*Naseer Samkranthi as Kambikaadu\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Shibu\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        = \n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|07|19}}\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      = \n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = \n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   = Kaargo Cinemas\n| prev_title = Katheyondu Shuruvagide\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\nLyrics are written by [[Manu Manjith]] and Vinayak Sasikumar, all music is composed by [[Sachin Warrier]] and Vignesh Baskaran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/shibu-teaser-released/articleshow/69539631.cms|title=Shibu teaser released - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Artist(s)\n| title5 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length6 = \n| title6 = \n| length5 = \n| length4 = \n| title1 = Aliyukayayi\n| title4 = \n| all_writing = \n| length3 = {{Duration|03:55}}\n| extra3 = Anwar Sadut\n| title3 = Oru Poo Chendu\n| length2 = {{Duration|04:00}}\n| extra2 = [[KS Harisankar]]\n| title2 = Pularum Vare\n| length1 = {{Duration|04:21}}\n| extra1 = [[Karthik (singer)]]\n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film released on 19 July 2019 across 80 screens in Kerala, to positive reviews from the critics as well as the audience.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.bookmyshow.com/ahmedabad/movies/shibu/ET00097537?fbrefresh=1|title=Shibu Movie (2019) {{!}} Reviews, Cast & Release Date in Ahmedabad|last=BookMyShow|website=BookMyShow|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://onlookersmedia.com/reviews/shibu-malayalam-movie-review/|title=\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d36\u0d15\u0d33\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e '\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 '|date=2019-07-19|website=Entertainment|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\nShibu released on [[Amazon prime]] on January 31, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Shibu-Karthik/dp/B084DP3PJZ/ref=mp_s_a_1_3?keywords=shibu&qid=1580796596&sr=8-3|title=Amazon prime|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical Reception ===\n\nPranav Prasad of telegraph Star gave 4 out of 5 and stated \"Absolute bliss to watch the lead pair Karthik Ramakrishnan and Anju Kurian on the big screen. The breezy love story is a must-watch. One needs to definitely watch the chemistry between the characters.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphstar.com/shibu-movie-review-and-rating-karthik-ramakrishnan-anju-kurian/|title=Shibu Movie Review And Rating {{!}} Karthik Ramakrishnan, Anju Kurian {{!}} Telegraph Star|last=Prasad|first=Pranav|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Anandh Vishnu of Samayam rated 2.5 out of 5.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://malayalam.samayam.com/malayalam-cinema/movie-review/salim-kumar-karthik-ramakrishnan-starrer-shibu-malayalam-movie-review-rating/moviereview/70286729.cms|title=\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41|date=2019-07-19|website=Samayam Malayalam|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Deepika Jayaram of Times of India Wrote \"What might strike a chord is the music by Sachin Warrier, which is meticulously composed to suit the narrative.\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Shibu Movie Review {2.0/5}: Critic Review of Shibu by Times of India|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/shibu/movie-review/70291062.cms|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Chandra Mohan Gopinath stated \"shibu is saved by the turn of events towards the closing stages\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/chandrascinemathoughts/posts/1289026781262546|title=Chandra's Cinema Thoughts|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{IMDB title|id=tt10405902}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shibu movie}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Sachin Warrier]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian action drama films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2019 Indian Malayalam-language film}}\n{{Use Indian English|date = October 2019}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date = October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Shibu\n| image          = Shibu movie poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Shibu movie poster\n| director       = Arjun Prabhakaran & Gokul Ramakrishnan\n| producer       = Kaargo Cinemas\n| screenplay     = Arjun , Gokul & Praneesh Vijayan\n| story          = \n| starring       = [[Karthik Ramakrishnan]] <br/> [[Anju Kurian]] <br/>[[Salim Kumar]] <br/> [[Biju Kuttan]]\n| music          = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| cinematography = Shabeer Ahammed\n| editing        = Noufal Abdullah\n| studio         = Kaargo Cinemas\n| distributor    = UK studios\n| released       = {{Film date|2019|07|19|df=y}}\n| runtime        = 122 minutes\n| country        = India\n| language       = Malayalam\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|50|L}}\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|95|L}}\n}}\n'''''Shibu'''''  is a 2019 Indian [[Malayalam]]-language film directed by duo directors Arjun Prabhakaran & Gokul Ramakrishnan, written by Praneesh and produced by Kaargo Cinemas.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiaglitz.com/the-story-of-dileep-fan-releases-its-first-look-poster-malayalam-news-212229|title='Aravindante Athidhikal' release date is here! - Malayalam News|date=2018-04-23|website=IndiaGlitz.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.southlive.in/movie/film-news/shibu-malayalam-movie-teaser-is-out/|title=\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d46 \u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2e\u0d28\u0d4b\u0d39\u0d30\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41; \u0d1f\u0d40\u0d38\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d {{!}} Southlive Malayalam: Kerala News, Malayalam News, Breaking News, Movie News, Political News|last=jo|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> It features an [[ensemble cast]] led by Karthik, [[Anju Kurian]], [[Salim Kumar]], [[Biju Kuttan]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-details/shibu/movieshow/69968971.cms|title='Shibu malayalam movie' times of india article}}</ref> [[Sachin Warrier]] composed the music for the film.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://malayalam.indianexpress.com/entertainment/dileep-fan-movie-shibu-first-look/|title=\u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d4d \u0d06\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u2018\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41\u2019 \u0d0e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41|date=2018-04-23|website=Indian Express Malayalam|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> and Movie was released on July 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sify.com/movies/shibu-to-release-this-june-news-malayalam-tf3jLjfegifeh.html|title='Shibu' to release this June|website=Sify|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/movies/movie-news/2019/06/04/shibu-malayalam-movie-trailer.html|title=\u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d4d \u0d06\u0d30\u0d3e\u0d27\u0d15\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d02; \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 \u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d46\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d|website=ManoramaOnline|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nShibu(Played by Karthik Ramakrishnan) is a young guy from small town who is an aspiring film maker, he tries hard to achieve his dreams, but gets rejected by all.Then he hears about a Film institute and he manages to convince his family and joins film institute.There he instead of learning about cinema gets confused. Later he met with a girl named Kalyani ([[Anju Kurian]]) in a match-making meet and how their aspirations brings them together forms rest of the story.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianetnews.com/topic/shibu-movie|title=shibu movie: Latest News, Photos, Videos on shibu movie {{!}} Asianetnews.com|website=www.asianetnews.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.vellinakshatram.com/online/news/shibu-malayalam-movie-traile_2019-06-04.php|title=\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4d \u0d26\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d40\u0d2a\u0d47\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d28\u0d46 \u0d12\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d1a\u0d2f\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d2a\u0d46\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f \u0d24\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d4b ? : \u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 \u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d46\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d7c \u0d0e\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d3f !!!|website=www.vellinakshatram.com/online/|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n==Production==\n\nIn 2018 Arjun and Gokul, who debuted with the movie '32aam Adhyayam 23aam Vaakyam' is all set to start working on their next project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nowrunning.com/movie/22623/malayalam/shibu/|title=Shibu (2019) Shibu Malayalam Movie|website=NOWRUNNING|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Titled 'Shibu movie' The film has music by Sachin Warrier. Sachin wrote about it, \"\u2018Omal Kanmani\u2019 composed by Bijibal sir from the 2015 movie \u201832aam Adhyayam 23aam Vaakyam\u2019 is a song that's close to heart among the ones I\u2019ve sung so far. The directors of the movie, Arjun and Gokul came to me to narrate a story recently, and I had a lot of fun listening to it. I believe it'll turn out to be an interesting film. Super happy to associate with Arjun and Gokul, as a composer in their second film\" says Sachin Warrier.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.desimartini.com/news/malayalam/director-duo-gokul-and-arjun-to-work-on-their-next-film-article75395.htm|title=Director duo Gokul And Arjun To Work On Their Next Film|date=2018-02-02|website=Desimartini|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.malayalamcinema.com/movies/profile/shibu|title=malayalamcinema.com, Official website of AMMA, Malayalam Film news, Malayalam Movie Actors & Actress, Upcoming Malayalam movies|website=www.malayalamcinema.com|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref name=\":0\" /> Arun Gopi director of [[Dileep]] starer movie [[Ramaleela]] released first look poster of the film on April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/another-hardcore-fan-based-movie-this-time-for-dileep/articleshow/63921957.cms|title=Another hardcore fan based movie, this time for Dileep - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref> Actor  [[Dileep]] released trailer of the film on june 2019<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://onlookersmedia.in/videos/dileep-releases-trailer-shibu/|title=Dileep releases the trailer of Shibu|last=Madhu|first=Vignesh|date=2019-06-04|website=onlookersmedia|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.asianetnews.com/entertainment/dileep-releases-teaser-of-shibu--pp0mb6|title=\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d3f\u0d2e\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d2a\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e\u0d41 '\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41'\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d1f\u0d40\u0d38\u0d7c|website=Asianet News Network Pvt Ltd|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n\n== Cast ==\n\n* Karthik Ramakrishnan as Shibu\n* [[Anju Kurian]] as Kalyani\n* [[Salim Kumar]] as Dr. Thomas\n* [[Biju Kuttan]] as Prahladhan\n* Lukman Lukku as Habeeb\n*[[Vinod Kovoor|Vinod kovoor]] as Producer\n* Unni Rajan P Dev as Antappan\n*[[Sneha (actress)|Sneha]] as Kalyanis friend\n* Aiswarya Padmakumar as Suhara\n*[[Rajesh Sharma (Malayalam actor)|Rajesh Sharma]] as Satheesh Kupleri\n*[[Kannan|Kannan Sagar]] as Bhuvanan\n*Badra as Shibu's Mom\n*Kshama Krishnan as Sheeba\n*Sharan as Siddique\n*Sundarpandiyan as Police Officer\n* [[Kochu Preman]] as Eastman Narayanan\n*Naseer Samkranthi as Kambikaadu\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Shibu\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = [[Sachin Warrier]]\n| cover      = \n| alt        = \n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2019|07|19}}\n| recorded   = 2019\n| venue      = \n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = \n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   = Kaargo Cinemas\n| prev_title = Katheyondu Shuruvagide\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n\nLyrics are written by [[Manu Manjith]] and Vinayak Sasikumar, all music is composed by [[Sachin Warrier]] and Vignesh Baskaran.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/shibu-teaser-released/articleshow/69539631.cms|title=Shibu teaser released - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Artist(s)\n| title5 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length6 = \n| title6 = \n| length5 = \n| length4 = \n| title1 = Aliyukayayi\n| title4 = \n| all_writing = \n| length3 = {{Duration|03:55}}\n| extra3 = Anwar Sadut\n| title3 = Oru Poo Chendu\n| length2 = {{Duration|04:00}}\n| extra2 = [[KS Harisankar]]\n| title2 = Pularum Vare\n| length1 = {{Duration|04:21}}\n| extra1 = [[Karthik (singer)]]\n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Release ==\nThe film released on 19 July 2019 across 80 screens in Kerala, to positive reviews from the critics as well as the audience.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://in.bookmyshow.com/ahmedabad/movies/shibu/ET00097537?fbrefresh=1|title=Shibu Movie (2019) {{!}} Reviews, Cast & Release Date in Ahmedabad|last=BookMyShow|website=BookMyShow|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://onlookersmedia.com/reviews/shibu-malayalam-movie-review/|title=\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d23\u0d2f\u0d35\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d24\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d36\u0d15\u0d33\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d28\u0d3f\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e '\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41 '|date=2019-07-19|website=Entertainment|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\nShibu released on [[Amazon prime]] on January 31, 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Shibu-Karthik/dp/B084DP3PJZ/ref=mp_s_a_1_3?keywords=shibu&qid=1580796596&sr=8-3|title=Amazon prime|last=|first=|date=|website=www.amazon.com|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-02-04}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical Reception ===\n\nPranav Prasad of telegraph Star gave 4 out of 5 and stated \"Absolute bliss to watch the lead pair Karthik Ramakrishnan and Anju Kurian on the big screen. The breezy love story is a must-watch. One needs to definitely watch the chemistry between the characters.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.telegraphstar.com/shibu-movie-review-and-rating-karthik-ramakrishnan-anju-kurian/|title=Shibu Movie Review And Rating {{!}} Karthik Ramakrishnan, Anju Kurian {{!}} Telegraph Star|last=Prasad|first=Pranav|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Anandh Vishnu of Samayam rated 2.5 out of 5.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://malayalam.samayam.com/malayalam-cinema/movie-review/salim-kumar-karthik-ramakrishnan-starrer-shibu-malayalam-movie-review-rating/moviereview/70286729.cms|title=\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d2c\u0d41|date=2019-07-19|website=Samayam Malayalam|language=ml|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Deepika Jayaram of Times of India Wrote \"What might strike a chord is the music by Sachin Warrier, which is meticulously composed to suit the narrative.\"<ref>{{Citation|title=Shibu Movie Review {2.0/5}: Critic Review of Shibu by Times of India|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movie-reviews/shibu/movie-review/70291062.cms|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref> Chandra Mohan Gopinath stated \"shibu is saved by the turn of events towards the closing stages\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/chandrascinemathoughts/posts/1289026781262546|title=Chandra's Cinema Thoughts|website=www.facebook.com|language=en|access-date=2020-01-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n\n* {{IMDB title|id=tt10405902}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Shibu movie}}\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:2010s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Sachin Warrier]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Indian action drama films]]\n[[Category:2019 films]]\n", "name_user": "Nallavan88", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shibu_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Chestnut-rumped heathwren", "text_new": "{{speciesbox\n| name = Chestnut-rumped heathwren\n| image = Chestnut- Rumped Heathwren small fx.jpg\n| status = LC\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name=IUCN>{{cite journal | author =BirdLife International | title = ''Hylacola pyrrhopygia'' | journal = [[IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume=2012 | page =e.T22704604A39302518  | year =2012 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2012-1.RLTS.T22704604A39302518.en }}</ref>\n| genus = Hylacola\n| species = pyrrhopygia\n| authority = ([[Nicholas Aylward Vigors|Vigors]] & [[Thomas Horsfield|Horsfield]], 1827)\n| synonyms = *''Calamanthus pyrrhopygia pyrrhopygia'' <small>Christidis and Boles (2008)</small>\n*''Hylacola pyrrhopygius pyrrhopygius'' <small>Sibley and Monroe (1990, 1993)</small>}}\nThe '''chestnut-rumped heathwren''' (''Hylacola pyrrhopygia'') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Acanthizidae]].\nIt is [[Endemism|endemic]] to temperate and subtropical forests of [[Australia]].\n\n==Taxonomy==\nThe generic name ''Hylacola'' derives from the Greek ''hul\u0113'' 'woodland' and the Latin ''-cola'' 'dweller'.<ref name=Helm>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Helm_Dictionary_of_Scientific_Bird_Names_by_James_A._Jobling|title=Helm Dictionary of Scientific Bird-names|last=Jobling|first=James A.|accessdate = 2020-04-18}}</ref> The specific epithet ''pyrrhopygia'' derives from Greek ''purrhos'' 'flame-coloured, red' and ''puge'' 'rump'.<ref name=Helm></ref> It is also known colloqiually as the scrub warbler.<ref name=Pizzey></ref>\nThere are three subspecies: ''Hylacola pyrrhopygia pyrrhopygia'' in New South Wales and Victoria; ''H. p. parkeri'' in the [[Mt Lofty Ranges]] of South Australia; and ''H. p. pedleri'' in the southern [[Flinders Ranges]] of South Australia.<ref name=Gregory>Gregory, P. (2020). \"Chestnut-rumped Heathwren (Hylacola pyrrhopygia), version 1.0.\" In ''Birds of the World'' (J. del Hoyo, A. Elliott, J. Sargatal, D. A. Christie, and E. de Juana, Editors). Cornell Lab of Ornithology, Ithaca, NY, USA. https://doi.org/10.2173/bow.chrhea1.01</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe chestnut-rumped heathwren is a small bushland bird with an olive-brown back, reddish-brown rump, and streaked brown-on-white chest. There is a terminal grey band on the tail. Both sexes have a prominent white eyebrow; eyes are yellow, while bill, legs, and feet are grey.<ref name=mdahlem>{{cite web|title=Chestnut-rumped Heathwren|url=http://www.mdahlem.net/birds/17/chrhwren.php|website=Mdahlem.net}}</ref> It measures {{convert|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} in length.<ref name = \"Campbell\"/>\n\n==Distribution and habitat==\nThe chestnut-rumped heathwren occurs in southeastern Australia from the [[Granite Belt]] of southeast [[Queensland]] through eastern [[New South Wales]], [[Victoria]], and southeast [[South Australia]].<ref name=Morcombe>Morcombe, Michael (2012) ''Field Guide to Australian Birds''. Pascal Press, Glebe, NSW. Revised edition. {{ISBN|978174021417-9}}</ref><ref name=birdata>{{cite web|url=https://birdata.birdlife.org.au/explore#map=-27.8587126_141.4881509_5&species_id=498|title=Birdata map:chestnut-rumped heathwren|accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref> In Victoria, it ranges inland to the [[Grampians]] and [[Bendigo]] region, but is more usual in coastal parts.<ref name=Pizzey>Pizzey, Graham; Doyle, Roy (1980) A Field Guide to the Birds of Australia. Collins Publishers, Sydney. ISBN 073222436-5</ref> In New South Wales, it occurs inland as far as the [[Warrumbungles]] and Temora.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> Scattered populations occur in the [[Flinders Ranges|Flinders]] and [[Mt Lofty Ranges]], and the [[Fleurieu Peninsula]] of South Australia.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> Its preferred habitats are [[heath]]s of coastal, mountain and hinterland areas, and the dense undergrowth of forests and woodland.<ref>Simpson, Ken, Day, N. and Trusler, P. (6th edn., 1999). ''Field Guide to the Birds of Australia''. Ringwood, Victoria: Penguin Books Australia {{ISBN|067087918-5}}.</ref><ref name=Morcombe></ref><ref name=Slater>Slater, Peter (1974) ''A Field Guide to Australian Birds: Passerines''. Adelaide: Rigby. ISBN 085179813-6</ref> It is sedentary and uncommon within its range.<ref name=Morcombe></ref>\n\n==Behaviour and Breeding==\nThe chestnut-rumped heathwren is usually shy and secretive until the breeding season from July to November, when it will sing from a perch on a bush, though still staying partly concealed.<ref name=Morcombe></ref> Its song is a melodious \"chi-chi-tu-weet\", \"kwe-reep\" and suchlike notes in great variety, blended with mimicry of other birds.<ref nameMorcombe></ref><ref name=Slater></ref><ref name=Pizzey></ref> The chestnut-rumped heathwren builds a domed or globular nest on or near the ground in tussocks or dense shrubs.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> It is composed of dry grass stems, bark fibre and rootlets, often appearing untidy.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> A clutch of three or four eggs is laid and usually incubated by the female.<ref name=Morcombe></ref> The eggs, measuring {{convert|20|by|15|mm|in}} are salmon-pink, freckled with light chocolate-brown, more so at the larger end.<ref name=Pizzey></ref><ref name=Morcombe></ref>\n\n==Conservation==\nAlthough the population of chestnut heathwrens is declining,<ref name=IUCN></ref> the species is currently classified as [[least-concern species|Least Concern]] by the [[IUCN]]. However, it is listed as [[Endangered]] in South Australia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naturalresources.sa.gov.au/files/sharedassets/public/plants_and_animals/threatened_species/pa-fact-chestnutrumpedheathwrenmountloftyranges.pdf|publisher=Natural Resources: Adelaide and Mt Lofty Ranges|title=Threatened Species Profile:Chestnut-rumped Heathwren (Mount Lofty Ranges)}}</ref> and [[Vulnerable]] in Victoria,<ref name=\"DSE2007\">{{cite book | author = Victorian Department of Sustainability and Environment | title = Advisory List of Threatened Vertebrate Fauna in Victoria - 2007 | publisher = Department of Sustainability and Environment | year = 2007 | location = East Melbourne, Victoria | pages = 15 | url = | isbn = 978-1-74208-039-0 }}</ref> with continued [[habitat fragmentation|fragmentation]] and [[loss of habitat]] and predation by [[introduced species|introduced]] predators being regarded as the main pressures.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | refs =\n<ref name = \"Campbell\">{{cite book | title = Birds of Australia: A Photographic Guide | first = Iain | last = Campbell | first2 = Sam | last2 = Woods | first3 = Nick | last3 = Leseberg | year = 2015 | location = Princeton, NJ, US | publisher = Princeton University Press | page = 248 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=wFMCBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA248 | isbn = 978-0-691-15727-6}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q27075266}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:heathwren, chestnut-rumped}}\n[[Category:Hylacola|chestnut-rumped heathwren]]\n[[Category:Birds of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Birds of South Australia]]\n[[Category:Endemic birds of Australia]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1827|chestnut-rumped heathwren]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n", "text_old": "{{speciesbox\n| name = Chestnut-rumped heathwren\n| image = Chestnut- Rumped Heathwren small fx.jpg\n| status = LC\n| status_system = IUCN3.1\n| status_ref = <ref name=IUCN>{{cite journal | author =BirdLife International | title = ''Hylacola pyrrhopygia'' | journal = [[IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume=2012 | page =e.T22704604A39302518  | year =2012 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.2012-1.RLTS.T22704604A39302518.en }}</ref>\n| genus = Hylacola\n| species = pyrrhopygia\n| authority = ([[Nicholas Aylward Vigors|Vigors]] & [[Thomas Horsfield|Horsfield]], 1827)\n| synonyms = *''Calamanthus pyrrhopygia pyrrhopygia'' <small>Christidis and Boles (2008)</small>\n*''Hylacola pyrrhopygius pyrrhopygius'' <small>Sibley and Monroe (1990, 1993)</small>}}\nThe '''chestnut-rumped heathwren''' (''Hylacola pyrrhopygia'') is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Acanthizidae]].\nIt is [[Endemism|endemic]] to temperate and subtropical forests of [[Australia]].\n\n==Taxonomy==\nThe generic name ''Hylacola'' derives from the Greek ''hul\u0113'' 'woodland' and the Latin ''-cola'' 'dweller'.<ref name=Helm>{{cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/Helm_Dictionary_of_Scientific_Bird_Names_by_James_A._Jobling|title=Helm Dictionary of Scientific Bird-names|last=Jobling|first=James A.|accessdate = 2020-04-18}}</ref> The specific epithet ''pyrrhopygia'' derives from Greek ''purrhos'' 'flame-coloured, red' and ''puge'' 'rump'.<ref name=Helm></ref> It is also known colloqiually as the scrub warbler.<ref name=Pizzey></ref>\nThere are three subspecies: ''Hylacola pyrrhopygia pyrrhopygia'' in New South Wales and Victoria; ''H. p. parkeri'' in the [[Mt Lofty Ranges]] of South Australia; and ''H. p. pedleri'' in the southern [[Flinders Ranges]] of South Australia.<ref name=Gregory>Gregory, P. (2020). \"Chestnut-rumped Heathwren (Hylacola pyrrhopygia), version 1.0.\" In ''Birds of the World'' (J. del Hoyo, A. Elliott, J. Sargatal, D. A. Christie, and E. de Juana, Editors). Cornell Lab of Ornithology, Ithaca, NY, USA. https://doi.org/10.2173/bow.chrhea1.01</ref>\n\n==Description==\nThe chestnut-rumped heathwren is a small bushland bird with an olive-brown back, reddish-brown rump, and streaked brown-on-white chest. There is a terminal grey band on the tail. Both sexes have a prominent white eyebrow; eyes are yellow, while bill, legs, and feet are grey.<ref name=mdahlem>{{cite web|title=Chestnut-rumped Heathwren|url=http://www.mdahlem.net/birds/17/chrhwren.php|website=Mdahlem.net}}</ref> It measures {{convert|14|cm|in|abbr=on}} in length.<ref name = \"Campbell\"/>\n\n==Distribution and habitat==\nThe chestnut-rumped heathwren occurs in southeastern Australia from the [[Granite Belt]] of southeast [[Queensland]] through eastern [[New South Wales]], [[Victoria]], and southeast [[South Australia]].<ref name=Morcombe>Morcombe, Michael (2012) ''Field Guide to Australian Birds''. Pascal Press, Glebe, NSW. Revised edition. {{ISBN|978174021417-9}}</ref><ref name=birdata>{{cite web|url=https://birdata.birdlife.org.au/explore#map=-27.8587126_141.4881509_5&species_id=498|title=Birdata map:chestnut-rumped heathwren|accessdate=2020-04-17}}</ref> In Victoria, it ranges inland to the [[Grampians]] and [[Bendigo]] region, but is more usual in coastal parts.<ref name=Pizzey>Pizzey, Graham; Doyle, Roy (1980) A Field Guide to the Birds of Australia. Collins Publishers, Sydney. ISBN 073222436-5</ref> In New South Wales, it occurs inland as far as the [[Warrumbungles]] and Temora.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> Scattered populations occur in the [[Flinders Ranges|Flinders]] and [[Mt Lofty Ranges]], and the [[Fleurieu Peninsula]] of South Australia.<ref name=Pizzey></ref> Its preferred habitats are [[heath]]s of coastal, mountain and hinterland areas, and the dense undergrowth of forests and woodland.<ref>Simpson, Ken, Day, N. and Trusler, P. (6th edn., 1999). ''Field Guide to the Birds of Australia''. Ringwood, Victoria: Penguin Books Australia {{ISBN|067087918-5}}.</ref><ref name=Morcombe></ref> It is sedentary and uncommon within its range.<ref name=Morcombe></ref>\n\n==Conservation==\nAlthough the population of chestnut heathwrens is declining,<ref name=IUCN></ref> the species is currently classified as [[least-concern species|Least Concern]] by the [[IUCN]]. However, it is listed as [[Endangered]] in South Australia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.naturalresources.sa.gov.au/files/sharedassets/public/plants_and_animals/threatened_species/pa-fact-chestnutrumpedheathwrenmountloftyranges.pdf|publisher=Natural Resources: Adelaide and Mt Lofty Ranges|title=Threatened Species Profile:Chestnut-rumped Heathwren (Mount Lofty Ranges)}}</ref> and [[Vulnerable]] in Victoria,<ref name=\"DSE2007\">{{cite book | author = Victorian Department of Sustainability and Environment | title = Advisory List of Threatened Vertebrate Fauna in Victoria - 2007 | publisher = Department of Sustainability and Environment | year = 2007 | location = East Melbourne, Victoria | pages = 15 | url = | isbn = 978-1-74208-039-0 }}</ref> with continued [[habitat fragmentation|fragmentation]] and [[loss of habitat]] and predation by [[introduced species|introduced]] predators being regarded as the main pressures.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | refs =\n<ref name = \"Campbell\">{{cite book | title = Birds of Australia: A Photographic Guide | first = Iain | last = Campbell | first2 = Sam | last2 = Woods | first3 = Nick | last3 = Leseberg | year = 2015 | location = Princeton, NJ, US | publisher = Princeton University Press | page = 248 | url = https://books.google.com/books?id=wFMCBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA248 | isbn = 978-0-691-15727-6}}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q27075266}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:heathwren, chestnut-rumped}}\n[[Category:Hylacola|chestnut-rumped heathwren]]\n[[Category:Birds of New South Wales]]\n[[Category:Birds of South Australia]]\n[[Category:Endemic birds of Australia]]\n[[Category:Birds described in 1827|chestnut-rumped heathwren]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n", "name_user": "Rogermccart", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBehaviour and Breeding:ce", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chestnut-rumped_heathwren"}
{"title_page": "2020 LCS season", "text_new": "{{Short description|Eighth season of North America's League of Legends Championship Series}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox sports season\n| title              = 2020 LCS season\n| league             = [[League of Legends Championship Series|LCS]]\n| sport              = ''[[League of Legends]]''\n| duration           = {{nowrap|January 25 \u2013 April 19 (Spring)<br />June 20 \u2013 September 13 (Summer)}}\n| no_of_matches      =\n| no_of_teams        = 10\n| TV                 = '''English:''' [[ESPN2]], [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]], [[YouTube]]<br />'''Chinese:''' [[Huya Live|Huya]]\n| season             = Spring\n| top_seed           = [[Cloud9]]\n| MVP                = Robert \"Blaber\" Huang (C9)<ref>{{cite news |last1=Stavropoulos |first1=Andreas |title=C9 Blaber wins 2020 LCS Spring MVP award |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/c9-blaber-wins-2020-lcs-spring-mvp-award |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |work=Dot Esports |date=April 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Ousley |first1=Parkes |title=League of Legends: Cloud9 Blaber is your 2020 LCS Spring Split Honda MVP |url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/11001/cloud9-blaber-is-your-2020-lcs-spring-split-honda-mvp |accessdate=April 18, 2020 |work=InvenGlobal |date=April 17, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n| MVP_link           =\n| season_champ_name  =\n| season_champs      =\n| second_place       =\n<!-- Uncomment when results are final\n| season2            = Summer\n| top_seed2          =\n| MVP2               =\n| MVP_link2          =\n| season_champ2_name =\n| season_champs2     =\n| second_place2      =\n-->\n| seasonslist        =\n| seasonslistnames   = LCS\n| prevseason_link    = 2019 LCS season\n| prevseason_year    = 2019\n| nextseason_link    = 2021 LCS season\n| nextseason_year    = ''2021''\n}}\n\nThe '''2020 LCS season''' is the third year [[Sports franchise|under partnership]] and eighth overall of the [[League of Legends Championship Series|''League of Legends'' Championship Series]] (LCS), a professional [[esports]] league for the [[Multiplayer online battle arena|MOBA]] [[PC game]] ''[[League of Legends]]''. It is the first year that the league will use a [[Double-elimination tournament|double elimination bracket]] for its [[playoff format]]. Championship points and the regional finals were also removed from the [[League of Legends World Championship|World Championship]] qualification process.<ref name=\"Dot1\">{{cite news |last1=Esguerra |first1=Tyler |title=Riot changes LCS playoff format for 2020, will also remove NA regional qualifiers |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/riot-changes-lcs-playoff-format-for-2020-will-also-remove-na-regional-qualifiers |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |work=Dot Esports |date=January 8, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"TheGamer1\">{{cite news |last1=Rutledge |first1=Caroline |title=Riot Games Announces Major LCS Format Changes Ahead of 2020 Season |url=https://www.thegamer.com/riot-games-announces-lcs-format-changes-2020-season/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |work=TheGamer |date=January 8, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"GGIntel1\">{{cite news |last1=Stewart |first1=Jack |title=LCS introduces double elimination Playoffs and stronger Academy investment for 2020 |url=https://www.ggintel.com/articles/lcs-introduces-double-elimination-playoffs-and-stronger-academy-investment-for-2020 |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |work=GGIntel |date=January 8, 2020 |language=EN}}</ref><ref name=\"VP1\">{{cite news |last1=Kolev |first1=Radoslav |title=LCS restructures Worlds qualification method, finally introduces double elimination bracket |url=https://www.vpesports.com/leagueoflegends/lcs-restructures-worlds-qualification-method-finally-introduces-double-elimination-bracket/ |accessdate=January 18, 2020 |work=VPEsports |date=January 9, 2020}}</ref>\n\nThe spring split began on January 25 and was scheduled to conclude with the spring finals on April 19; however, due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|spread of COVID-19 in the United States]], the season was temporarily suspended on March 13.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Esguerra |first1=Tyler |title=Riot suspends LCS season, moves 2020 Spring Finals to Los Angeles |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/riot-suspends-lcs-season-moves-2020-spring-finals-to-los-angeles |accessdate=March 16, 2020 |work=Dot Esports |date=March 13, 2020}}</ref> Four days later, it was announced that the LCS would resume on March 20, with all matches being played online.\n\nThe summer split will begin on June 20 and conclude with the summer finals on September 13.<ref name=\"TheGamer1\"/><ref name=\"GGIntel1\"/>\n\n== League changes ==\n[[Riot Games]] announced several changes to the LCS on January 8.<ref name=\"Dot1\"/><ref name=\"TheGamer1\"/><ref name=\"GGIntel1\"/><ref name=\"VP1\"/>\n\n=== Playoff format ===\nFrom the 2020 season onwards, the LCS will use a double elimination bracket as its playoff format,<ref name=\"Dot1\"/><ref name=\"GGIntel1\"/><ref name=\"VP1\"/> similar to that which was adopted by the [[League of Legends European Championship|LEC]] the previous year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Esguerra |first1=Lawrence Tyler |title=LEC introduces a new season format for 2019 |url=https://www.dailyesports.gg/lec-introduces-new-season-format/ |accessdate=January 21, 2020 |work=Daily Esports |date=January 15, 2019}}</ref> The number of teams participating in the spring playoffs will remain unchanged at six, but the summer playoffs will include an additional two teams, bringing the total up to eight. Both splits will feature a winners' bracket and a losers' bracket, with the bottom two teams beginning in the losers' and the rest beginning in the winners'.<ref name=\"TheGamer1\"/><ref name=\"VP1\"/>\n\n=== Schedule ===\nThe LCS schedule was revised for the 2020 season. Four LCS games will broadcast each Saturday and Sunday instead of five, and two games will air during \"Monday Night League\", which will feature the two most popular matchups of the week.<ref name=\"TheGamer1\"/><ref name=\"GGIntel1\"/><ref name=\"VP1\"/> LCS commissioner Chris Greeley explained that this was done to give less popular teams and players more exposure and opportunities to develop their brand, as most viewers, he argued, only tune in to watch their favorite teams.<ref name=\"VP1\"/>\n\n=== International qualifications ===\nChampionship points and the regional finals were removed from the LCS prior to the start of the 2020 season.<ref name=\"TheGamer1\"/><ref name=\"GGIntel1\"/> The results of the spring split will only determine the LCS' representative for the [[Mid-Season Invitational]], and will no longer have any part in determining a team's future qualification for the World Championship. The summer champions, runners-up and third place team will qualify for the World Championship as the LCS' first, second and third seeds respectively.<ref name=\"VP1\"/>\n\n== Broadcasting ==\nThe English broadcast is available on the LoL Esports website, as well as on [[Twitch (service)|Twitch]]<ref>{{cite news |last1=Brathwaite |first1=Brandon |title=Riot Games Pilots Twitch Co-Streaming for NA LCS |url=https://esportsobserver.com/riot-games-co-streaming/ |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |work=The Esports Observer |date=September 14, 2018}}</ref> and [[YouTube]].<ref name=\"Matthiesen\">{{cite news |last1=Matthiesen |first1=Tom |title=League of Legends: Riot partners with Huya as exclusive platform to broadcast the LCS and LEC in China |url=https://www.invenglobal.com/articles/10211/riot-partners-with-huya-as-exclusive-platform-to-broadcast-the-lcs-and-lec-in-china |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |work=Inven Global |date=January 20, 2020 |language=en}}</ref> On January 20, Riot Games announced their official partnership with Chinese streaming service [[Huya Live|Huya]], giving them exclusive rights to the Chinese broadcast.<ref name=\"Matthiesen\"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Esguerra |first1=Tyler |title=Huya becomes newest exclusive LCS and LEC broadcaster in China |url=https://dotesports.com/league-of-legends/news/huya-becomes-newest-exclusive-lcs-and-lec-broadcaster-in-china |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |work=Dot Esports |date=January 20, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Murray |first1=Trent |title=Huya Secures Chinese Broadcast Rights for LCS, LEC |url=https://esportsobserver.com/lcslec-china-huya/ |accessdate=January 20, 2020 |work=The Esports Observer |date=January 20, 2020}}</ref> On April 8, it was announced that the spring playoffs would be aired on [[ESPN2]] and the ESPN App.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ocal |first1=Arda |title=LCS spring split playoff games to air on ESPN |url=https://www.espn.com/esports/story/_/id/29012471/lcs-spring-split-playoff-games-air-espn |accessdate=April 10, 2020 |work=ESPN |date=April 8, 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Spring ==\n\n=== Teams and rosters ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Team\n! colspan=\"5\" | Roster\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Coach\n|-\n! Top\n! Jungle\n! Mid\n! Bot\n! Support\n|-\n| '''[[100 Thieves]]'''\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} Ssumday\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Meteos (video game player)|Meteos]]\n| {{flagicon|AUS}} Ryoma\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Cody Sun]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Stunt\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Zikz\n|-\n| '''[[Cloud9]]'''\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} Licorice\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Blaber\n| {{flagicon|BEL}} Nisqy\n| {{flagicon|DEN}} Zven\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} Vulcan\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} Reapered\n|-\n| '''[[Counter Logic Gaming]]'''\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} Ruin\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Wiggily\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} Crown<br />{{flagicon|USA}} [[Pobelter]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} [[Stixxay]]<br />{{flagicon|KOR}} Wind\n| {{flagicon|CAN}} [[Smoothie (video game player)|Smoothie]]\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} SSONG\n|-\n| '''[[Dignitas (esports)|Dignitas]]'''\n| {{flagicon|KOR}} [[Huni (video game player)|Huni]]\n| {{flagicon|USA}} Akaadian<br />{{flagicon|USA}} Grig\n| {{flagicon|DEN}}